---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Container from '../../components/UI/Container.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Cookies Policy"
  metaTitle="Cookies Policy - All Leaders Initiative"
  metaDescription="Information about cookies and similar technologies used on our website."
  lang="en"
  alternateUrls={{ fr: '/cookies', en: '/en/cookies' }}
>
  <Container>
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto py-6">
      <h1 class="pt-[12vh] pb-6">Cookies Policy</h1>

      <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-8">
        <strong>Last updated:</strong> May 2024 | <strong>Version:</strong> 1.0
      </p>

      <div class="prose prose-sm max-w-none">
        <p class="lead mb-8">
          This policy describes the use of cookies and similar technologies on the website <strong
            >all-leaders.fr</strong
          >. A cookie is a small text file stored in your browser. This policy informs you of the
          nature, purpose and management of these files in accordance with the GDPR and
          ICO guidance.
        </p>

        <h2>1. What is a cookie?</h2>

        <p>
          A cookie is a small text file (between 4 and 8 kilobytes) stored locally in
          your browser when you visit a website. It allows the website to:
        </p>

        <ul>
          <li>Remember your preferences or session identifiers</li>
          <li>Measure website usage and audience</li>
          <li>Personalise content to your interests</li>
        </ul>

        <p>
          <strong>Cookies cannot:</strong> install viruses, execute code, access
          other files on your computer, or identify you without your prior consent.
        </p>

        <h2>2. Types of cookies used on all-leaders.fr</h2>

        <h3>2.1 Strictly necessary / Technical cookies</h3>

        <p>
          These cookies are essential for the technical operation of the website and security. They
          do not require your explicit consent, in accordance with the GDPR and ICO guidance.
        </p>

        <div class="overflow-x-auto mb-6">
          <table class="w-full border-collapse">
            <thead>
              <tr class="bg-gray-100">
                <th class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2 text-left">Cookie name</th>
                <th class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2 text-left">Issued by</th>
                <th class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2 text-left">Purpose</th>
                <th class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2 text-left">Duration</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr>
                <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2"><code>PHPSESSID</code></td>
                <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2">all-leaders.fr</td>
                <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2">User session management</td>
                <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2">End of session</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2"><code>__Secure-*</code></td>
                <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2">all-leaders.fr</td>
                <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2">Website security (authentication)</td
                >
                <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2">Depending on context</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2"
                  ><code>ali_consent_preferences</code></td
                >
                <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2">all-leaders.fr</td>
                <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2"
                  >Storage of your cookie consent choices</td
                >
                <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2">13 months</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

        <h3>2.2 Analytical and audience measurement cookies</h3>

        <p>
          <strong>Consent required.</strong> With your agreement, we use Google Analytics 4 (a Google LLC
          service) to measure and analyse the audience of our pages: number of visitors, most visited pages,
          session duration, devices and browsers used, source of traffic.
        </p>

        <p class="mb-4">
          <strong>Purposes:</strong> To understand how our visitors use the website in order to improve
          its content, performance and usability.
        </p>

        <p class="mb-6">
          <strong>Data collected:</strong> Data is aggregated and anonymised. Google Analytics
          does not collect your personal details directly, but associates your activity with a
          pseudonymised identifier.
        </p>

        <div class="overflow-x-auto mb-6">
          <table class="w-full border-collapse">
            <thead>
              <tr class="bg-gray-100">
                <th class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2 text-left">Name</th>
                <th class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2 text-left">Issued by</th>
                <th class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2 text-left">Purpose</th>
                <th class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2 text-left">Duration</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr>
                <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2"><code>_ga</code></td>
                <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2">Google</td>
                <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2">Distinguish unique visitors</td>
                <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2">2 years</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2"><code>_ga_[ID]</code></td>
                <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2">Google</td>
                <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2"
                  >Maintain session state and timeline</td
                >
                <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2">2 years</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2"><code>_gat</code></td>
                <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2">Google</td>
                <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2">Limit GA request rate</td>
                <td class="border border-gray-300 px-4 py-2">1 minute</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>

        <p>
          <strong>International transfer:</strong> Google may transfer this data to the United States
          on the basis of the "Data Privacy Framework" (DPF) approved by the European Commission. For
          more information, consult the <a
            href="https://policies.google.com/privacy"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer">Google privacy policy</a
          >.
        </p>

        <h3>2.3 Marketing and targeting cookies (where applicable)</h3>

        <p>
          <strong>Consent required.</strong> These cookies allow us to offer you content or
          advertisements tailored to your interests and to measure the effectiveness of our campaigns. They are
          generally used in conjunction with advertising partners.
        </p>

        <p class="text-sm mt-4">
          <em
            >Currently, no third-party marketing cookies are used on this website. Only
            Google Analytics 4 analytical cookies are enabled.</em
          >
        </p>

        <h2>3. Your consent and preferences</h2>

        <h3>3.1 Implied consent on first visit</h3>

        <p>
          On your first visit, a cookie consent banner is displayed. You have the option to:
        </p>

        <ul>
          <li><strong>Accept all cookies:</strong> including analytical and marketing</li>
          <li>
            <strong>Reject all cookies:</strong> only strictly necessary cookies will be
            installed
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Manage your preferences:</strong> refine your consent by category
          </li>
        </ul>

        <p class="mt-4">
          You retain complete control over your choices, even after your initial consent.
        </p>

        <h3>3.2 Change your preferences at any time</h3>

        <p class="mb-4">
          You can change your consent preferences at any time. You have several options:
        </p>

        <ul>
          <li>
            Click the button below to redisplay the consent banner and modify
            your choices
          </li>
          <li>Clear the cache and cookies from your browser</li>
          <li>Access the privacy/cookies settings in your browser</li>
        </ul>

        <div class="my-6 p-4 bg-blue-50 border-l-4 border-blue-500">
          <button
            id="cookie-manage"
            class="px-6 py-2.5 bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white font-semibold rounded transition-colors"
          >
            Manage my cookie preferences
          </button>
        </div>

        <h2>4. Local storage and retention period</h2>

        <p>
          Your consent choice is stored locally in your browser via
          localStorage under the key <code>ali_consent_preferences</code>. This file
          does not expire automatically and persists until you:
        </p>

        <ul>
          <li>Explicitly change your preferences via the button above</li>
          <li>Manually clear your browser's browsing data</li>
          <li>Uninstall your browser (session cookies only)</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>5. Browser-level cookie management</h2>

        <p>
          Independently of the choices offered by this website, you can manage or disable cookies
          directly in your browser settings. Here's how to do it depending on your
          browser:
        </p>

        <ul class="space-y-3">
          <li>
            <strong>Google Chrome:</strong> Settings → Privacy and security → Cookies and other
            site data
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Mozilla Firefox:</strong> Settings → Privacy → Cookies and site data
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Apple Safari:</strong> Preferences → Privacy → Manage website data
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Microsoft Edge:</strong> Settings → Privacy → Cookies and other site
            data
          </li>
        </ul>

        <p class="mt-6">
          <em
            ><strong>Warning:</strong> Disabling strictly necessary cookies may affect
            website functionality (authentication, security, preferences). We recommend
            disabling only analytical or marketing cookies.</em
          >
        </p>

        <h2>6. Opt-out of Google Analytics 4</h2>

        <p>
          If you do not wish your data to be collected by Google Analytics, you
          can install <a
            href="https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noopener noreferrer">the Google Analytics opt-out extension</a
          > directly in your browser.
        </p>

        <h2>7. Respect for children's privacy</h2>

        <p>
          The website is not intended for children under 16 years of age. No data is
          intentionally collected from children without the explicit consent of a legal guardian.
          If you are under 16, do not complete the contact forms.
        </p>

        <h2>8. Third-party policies and external links</h2>

        <p>
          This website may contain links to third-party websites or embed external content
          (videos, social networks, maps, etc.). These third parties have their own cookies policies,
          independent of ours. Consult their privacy policies respectively to understand
          their cookie usage.
        </p>

        <h2>9. Changes to this policy</h2>

        <p>
          This cookies policy may be updated at any time to reflect
          technological or regulatory changes. The applicable version is that in force
          at the time of your visit to the website.
        </p>

        <h2>10. Questions and contact</h2>

        <p>
          For any questions concerning this policy, the use of cookies or the exercise of
          your rights, please contact us at:
        </p>

        <p>
          <a href="mailto:contact@all-leaders.fr" class="font-semibold">contact@all-leaders.fr</a>
        </p>

        <p class="mt-6 pt-6 border-t border-gray-200">
          Also consult our <a href="/en/privacy" class="font-semibold"
            >privacy policy</a
          > for a complete overview of how we process your personal data.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </Container>
</Layout>

<style>
  h2 {
    font-size: 2rem;
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  h3 {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    margin-top: 0.5rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  ul li {
    text-align: center;
  }
</style>
